# T5f bridge loop resilience - 2026-05-23

Purpose: reduce the operational fragility of the bridge-backed autonomy path
while native Pentagon trigger polling remains blocked.

## Problem

The persistent LaunchAgent bridge was running, but launchctl showed a historical
non-zero exit state. The stderr log showed the loop process had previously
crashed on transient external conditions:

~~~text
TypeError: fetch failed
cause: ConnectTimeoutError: Connect Timeout Error
code: UND_ERR_CONNECT_TIMEOUT

TypeError: fetch failed
cause: Error: getaddrinfo ENOTFOUND ieetsizejvdpsvaiuukb.supabase.co
code: ENOTFOUND

Error: GET /rest/v1/agent_triggers?... failed 401:
code=PGRST303 message=JWT expired
~~~

These failures do not mean a target trigger is invalid. They mean the bridge
loop was treating network/auth drift as a process-fatal condition, relying on
launchd restart instead of preserving a stable poller process.

## Repair

scripts/pentagon-trigger-bridge.mjs now wraps persistent loop iterations in a
catch block that:

- logs a structured loop_error JSON event to stderr.
- preserves one-shot mode as fail-fast.
- refreshes the Pentagon session after JWT-expired loop errors.
- logs session_refreshed_after_loop_error or
  session_refresh_failed_after_loop_error for auditability.
- continues polling after the loop interval instead of exiting.

This does not repair native Pentagon polling. It makes the current bridge
mitigation more reliable while the native app remains the product blocker.

## Validation

~~~text
$ node --check scripts/pentagon-trigger-bridge.mjs
exit: 0

$ node scripts/pentagon-trigger-bridge.mjs --dry-run --limit 1 --max-age-seconds 180
status: ok
processed: 1
trigger_id: b416475a-9a79-46bb-8e14-96754b15ce56
conversation_id: 1e05c006-7801-479c-941c-8460e6faa55a
agent_id: 3401eaa3-6bde-4373-b418-a09e78f6bad4
created_at: 2026-05-23T13:06:13.132426+00:00

$ launchctl kickstart -k gui/501/run.pentagon.trigger-bridge
exit: 0

$ launchctl print gui/501/run.pentagon.trigger-bridge
state = running
program = /opt/homebrew/bin/node
pid = 98524
runs = 3102
last terminating signal = Terminated: 15
~~~

The latest terminating signal was the intentional kickstart restart, not a new
script crash. The current LaunchAgent process is running the patched script.

## Current boundary

Verified improvement: bridge loop resilience.

Still not complete: native Pentagon autonomous handoff. The full goal still
requires native trigger polling or a documented target-turn primitive to activate
recipient agents within the declared window without the external bridge.
